  "text": "A rare variant of breast cancer, secretory breast cancer, has a characteristic recurrent translocation between ETS variant 6 (ETV6) and neurotrophic tyrosine kinase type 3 (NTRK3), t(12;15)(p13;q25) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This translocation appears to be the initial hit required for formation of secretory breast cancer. Retroviral transfer of ETV6-NTRK3 into murine mammary epithelial cells resulted in transformed cells that readily formed tumours in nude mice.",
